{"TopicId":175793,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Has anybody collected a surface sample from an Easter Egg?","CreatedByName":"Duck McFuddle","CreatedById":188882,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-10T13:09:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Duck McFuddle","CreatedById":188882,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-10T13:09:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have tried to get on top of a monolith through multiple skydiving attempts so I can collect a surface sample, but no luck so far. Has anybody already done this? It could be fun. You could easily get onto a Mun arch but I don\u0027t know where they are on the Mun and am too lazy to find out, so I\u0027m still working on the Monolith near \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-10T13:09:47Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2018 01:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Duck McFuddle\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystifeid","CreatedById":187479,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-10T15:02:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022RIAWxap.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/RIAWxap.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T01:42:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022744screenshot161.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022609\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/744screenshot161.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystifeid","CreatedById":187479,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T03:24:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurious that I see a report from Kerbin\u0027s Shores:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224gJ3aJs.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/4gJ3aJs.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-11T03:24:27Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2018 03:24  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by mystifeid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T07:07:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/1jHvAxf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u00221jHvAxf.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was recently\u00A0on a Mun Arch\u00A0and had the same question in mind. No problem getting that sample either. I know the pic isn\u0027t evidence of the sample being possible... but its pretty, so like it\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T07:48:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528687450\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187479\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mystifeid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, mystifeid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurious that I see a report from Kerbin\u0027s Shores:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe monolith sits right on the border between the two. I found that out recently and now use it as a marker whenever I am farming at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystifeid","CreatedById":187479,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T09:30:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397287\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528703321\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe monolith sits right on the border between the two. I found that out recently and now use it as a marker whenever I am farming at the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m confused. Driving my rover around, once I\u0027m in either one I have to drive quite a way past the monolith before the biome changes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo - halfway back to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E, I\u0027m still in Kerbin\u0027s Shores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022U1bpgIY.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/U1bpgIY.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce I\u0027m in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E though and turn around and go the other way, I have to go nearly to the water\u0027s edge before it changes back to Kerbin\u0027s Shores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00229H95DkT.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/9H95DkT.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe the Kerbal sitting on top of the monolith is messing things up. I don\u0027t know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T09:50:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t know. I just know that as soon as I pass the Monolith, I\u0027ve got Shores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystifeid","CreatedById":187479,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T09:54:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397305\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528710607\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t know. I just know that as soon as I pass the Monolith, I\u0027ve got Shores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting that both the narrow band scanner and the surface scanner don\u0027t register the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E biomes - to them it\u0027s all part of Biome: Shores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KUVEaGJ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/KUVEaGJ.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T09:55:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528710844\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187479\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mystifeid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, mystifeid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting that both the narrow band scanner and the surface scanner don\u0027t register the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E biomes - to them it\u0027s all part of Biome: Shores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s normal, also if you jump and take an eva report, you\u0027re flying at the shores and not in any \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003Eksc\u003C/abbr\u003E biome. I think the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E biomes are special in some way and not part of the actual biome map.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T10:36:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E minibiomes are called minibiomes for a reason. They are very localized regions within the shores biome, and you have to do specific things to access them (ie. be touching the ground or a building).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yes, there is a hysteresis effect on crossing biome boundaries. They don\u0027t flip to a new biome immediately, even though you crossed a boundary.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daniel Prates","CreatedById":172769,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T20:41:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528710929\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s normal, also if you jump and take an eva report, you\u0027re flying at the shores and not in any \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003Eksc\u003C/abbr\u003E biome. I think the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E biomes are special in some way and not part of the actual biome map.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat happena with flying crew reports too. In the\u00A0high end of the armosphere\u00A0 you get an upper atmosphere report anywhere,\u00A0 and in the low end,\u00A0 you get different reports for different biomes. It will depend on the experiment I guess. Aome other experiments only provide \u0022flying low\u0022 and \u0022flyung high\u0022 reports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-11T20:42:06Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2018 08:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Daniel Prates\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T01:06:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528749693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172769\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Daniel Prates\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Daniel Prates said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat happena with flying crew reports too. In the\u00A0high end of the armosphere\u00A0 you get an upper atmosphere report anywhere,\u00A0 and in the low end,\u00A0 you get different reports for different biomes. It will depend on the experiment I guess. Aome other experiments only provide \u0022flying low\u0022 and \u0022flyung high\u0022 reports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but you get eva flying reports from every biome in the game, except those special \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daniel Prates","CreatedById":172769,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T12:00:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397709\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528765581\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but you get eva flying reports from every biome in the game, except those special \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts indeed strange how some places in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E are proper biomes for some experiments,\u00A0 but aren\u0027t for others.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo comment the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, I too think that there is room for improvement here. A surface sample from an anomaly would give you all the more reason to go there. Tracking and landing next to the polar cap\u0027s saucer,\u00A0 for one, should at least reward you with decent science (and it\u0027s a saucer,\u00A0 no less!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystifeid","CreatedById":187479,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T15:41:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397919\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528804852\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172769\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Daniel Prates\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Daniel Prates said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo comment the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, I too think that there is room for improvement here. A surface sample from an anomaly would give you all the more reason to go there. Tracking and landing next to the polar cap\u0027s saucer,\u00A0 for one, should at least reward you with decent science (and it\u0027s a saucer,\u00A0 no less!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood idea!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MZxyycf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/MZxyycf.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}